# Plan and todo quality

When writing a plan or todo list (e.g. in plan mode):

- **Atomic**: One concrete outcome per item—no "and also" or multiple deliverables in one step.
- **Clear**: Each item states what to do and where (file/module/command) so there's no guesswork.
- **Junior-dev implementable**: Someone with basic context can complete an item without needing to design the solution; the item is the instruction.
